The Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs department says enforcing bylaws in Alexandra, is a challenge. JOHANNESBURG - The Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs department says enforcing bylaws in Alexandra, is a challenge. Last week, the Red Ants demolished about 80 illegal structures in the Johannesburg township. READ: Blame game as structures are demolished in Alex Cogta spoke extensively about its role in the area at Monday's hearing by the Human Rights Commission, looking at issues in the township.
"We have established that the city has developed numerous bylaws. The ability to enforce them is a challenge…the difficulty that comes with enforcing them comes from the community dynamics. The distance that emerges from the government and community must be attended to -- the level of lawlessness is quite dramatic", said Gauteng Cogta HOD, Thandeka Mbassa.